title: Indians now account for over 10% of US visa applicants
description: The US embassy here said on Thursday it has processed over 10 lakh non-immigrant visa applications so far this year, a first for India. This is almost 20% more than the numbers processed in pre-Covid 2019 and 2022. "Indians now represent over 10% of all visa applicants worldwide, including 20% of all student visa applicants, and 65% of all H & L category (employment) visa applicants," the embassy said while welcoming this growth.

title: Speaker refers Bidhuri case to privileges panel
description: Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla has referred complaints of some MPs against BJP's Ramesh Bidhuri for using "derogatory" words against BSP's Danish Ali in the House to the Privileges Committee.

title: Drone poses midair danger to 2 planes in Bengaluru
HC bail order Unexecuted 3 yrs: Lower court, Jail communication failure
80kg cocaine worth ₹800 crore found abandoned in Gujarat
Manipur unrest purely an internal matter of India: Zomi Council
description: The Zomi Council Steering Committee, one of the organisations that represent Zomi-Kuki-Hmar tribes from Manipur, has disengaged itself from efforts to internationalise the ethnic strife, with many civil society outfits seeking to highlight the clashes in the state to embarrass India on international platforms and even demanding foreign intervention.

title: Row over Bengal cops 'snooping' on Raj Bhavan
ED summons Abhishek again
In fragile Himalayas, Uttarakhand plans ski resorts, ropeways
description: In what the government of Uttarakhand feels could lead to a major boost in the state's infrastructure - especially those involving the tourism sector - CM Pushkar Singh Dhami during a visit to London has signed MoUs worth Rs 8,000 crore with focus on the development of skiing destinations and ropeway projects. In all, MoUs worth Rs 11,000 crore have been inked with various companies.

title: LeT operative's mystery killing in Pakistan spooks ISI
description: The killing of Maulana Ziaur Rahman, a cleric, at a park in Karachi's Gulistan-e-Jauhar would have attracted the attention of his kin, his friends and those convinced of his religious piety. In Pakistan, several of the clerics are engaged in extra-religious gigs with some of them getting regularly bumped off for various reasons.

title: His work transformed lives of millions: PM Modi
description: The death of pre-eminent agriculture scientist MS Swaminathan has been met with deep condolences from President Droupadi Murmu, Prime Minister Narendra Modi, home minister Amit Shah, and other leaders. They all praise Swaminathan as a visionary who worked tirelessly to achieve food security for India. President Murmu highlights his rich legacy in Indian agriculture science, while PM Modi emphasizes his groundbreaking work that transformed the lives of millions.

title: Ujjain rape case accused injured in bid to flee
description: An autorickshaw driver was arrested in Ujjain on Thursday for the rape of a minor girl, whose video clip of being shooed away by people while pleading for help in a bleeding, half-naked state has shocked the country. The accused, Bharat Soni, tried to escape from custody when he was taken to the crime spot for forensic investigation, and fell on the road, injuring himself.

title: Cloud over alliance as Congress MLA held in Punjab
description: Punjab Police arrested Congress MLA Sukhpal Singh Khaira on Thursday morning at his Chandigarh residence in connection with a case under the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances (NDPS) Act, registered against him in Jalalabad of Fazilka district in 2015.

title: Srinagar SSP repatriated to Manipur amid fresh unrest
description: Amid a fresh bout of violent protests in Manipur, this time over the kidnapping and killing of two students, the central government has cut short the inter-cadre deputation of Srinagar’s senior superintendent of police (SSP) Rakesh Balwal, a Manipur cadre IPS officer, and repatriated him to his parent cadre.  ​​The Manipur government had sought his premature repatriation around 20 days back, as per sources.

title: Varanasi court junks plea to stop Gyanvapi ASI survey
description: A Varanasi court rejected Thursday a plea by the Gyanvapi mosque management to stop the Archaeological Survey of India’s (ASI) scientific study and survey of the complex, adjacent to the Kashi Vishwanath temple in the city.

title: China seizes pole position as Maldives votes for president
description: India is facing a potential diplomatic challenge in the Maldives, where the opposition candidate supported by pro-China leader Abdulla Yameen is favored to win the presidential runoff. This outcome threatens India's efforts to counter China's influence in the region. The runoff was triggered because no candidate in the September 9 election received the required majority.

title: EAM S Jaishankar meets US secretary of state Antony Blinken
description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar on Thursday met US secretary of state Antony Blinken in Washington. The meeting comes amid serious diplomatic tensions between India and Canada stirred by the killing of a Khalistani terrorist.

title: Karima Baloch's husband blames Pak's ISI for her killing, asks Canada to reopen case
description: The husband of Baloch political activist Karima Baloch, who was killed in Toronto in 2020, accused Pakistan's ISI of her murder and called on the Canadian government to reopen the investigation. He participated in a protest in Geneva organized by the Baloch National Movement (BNM) to demand justice for Karima and other Baloch activists killed in Pakistan and abroad.

title: Centre opens up new areas north of Pangong for tourists
description: The home ministry has opened up for tourists two forbidden areas close to the strategic Chang Chenmo sector north of Pangong lake in Ladakh, even as the border standoff with China runs into its fourth year. A September 14 circular by the ministry also allows foreign tourists to stay overnight in Hanle, a Mecca for stargazers 254 km east of Leh.

title: Breaking curfew, mob tries to attack Manipur CM's house
description: A mob tried to attack chief minister N Biren Singh's empty ancestral house on Thursday night, despite a security clampdown and curfew in the Imphal valley.Security forces, however, were successful in foiling the attempt after firing in the air.Singh lives in a separate, well-guarded official residence in the centre of the state's capital.

title: Ramaswamy says he wants to end birthright citizenship in US
description: Vivek Ramaswamy, a Republican presidential candidate, has pledged to end birthright citizenship for children of illegal immigrants if elected to the White House. He argues that the interpretation of the 14th Amendment does not grant citizenship to children of illegal immigrants. Ramaswamy's position echoes former President Donald Trump's proposal in 2015, but he never implemented it due to the consensus in the US to follow the Supreme Court's interpretation.

title: Gunman kills 2 in twin shootings in Netherlands
description: Twin shootings in Rotterdam have resulted in fatalities, according to the police. The shootings occurred in a flat and a nearby medical center, with fires breaking out in both locations. Elite police units searched for the suspect, a 32-year-old man, who was armed with a handgun. The motive for the attack is currently unknown.

title: Asian Games Hockey: India get 'complacency scare' in win over Japan
description: Young striker Abhishek fired two goals as India beat defending champions Japan 4-2 to register their third consecutive victory and take a giant step towards semi-final of the men's hockey competition at the Asian Games. Abhishek (13th, 48th minutes) scored two field goals, while Mandeep Singh (24th) and Amit Rohidas (34th) were the other scorers for India.

title: Priyanka Choudhary: I was body shamed for being underweight
description: Actress Priyanka Chahar Choudhary, known for her appearance on Bigg Boss 16, opened up about her journey in the entertainment industry. Starting as a VJ in Jaipur, she faced ups and downs before gaining popularity. Choudhary spoke about her passion for acting and her supportive father. She also discussed the pressure of having a male child in her family and her experience with body shaming.

title: Ujjain horror: Auto rickshaw driver held for minor's rape
description: Accused Bharat Soni, detained during the probe, tried to escape when the police took him to the crime spot for recreating crime scene and collect evidence like torn clothes, said Mahakal police station in-charge Ajay Verma.

title: Muddy waters at foggy bottom: US-India blues over Canada spat
description: Tensions between India and Canada over the alleged involvement of New Delhi in the assassination of a Sikh extremist are impacting India-US bilateral engagements. The US State Department has urged India to cooperate with the Canadian investigation into the incident.

title: Manish Malhotra to design new uniform for Air India
description: Designer Manish Malhotra will design new uniforms for over 10,000 Air India employees on the frontline, including cabin crew, cockpit crew, ground and security staff as part of the Tata Group airline’s new global brand identity amid an ongoing modernisation programme. Air India says it expects to rollout the new uniforms by the end of this year.

title: World Cup: Ashwin replaces injured Axar in India squad
description: Veteran off-spinner Ravichandran Ashwin was on Thursday named in India's final 15-man squad for the ODI World Cup. Ashwin, 37, replaces Axar Patel, who had been named in the provisional squad but did not recover from his left quadriceps strain.

title: Pakistan is a weaker team than India at this moment: Waqar
description: Legendary pacer Waqar Younis rated India a better side over Pakistan going into the World Cup while basing his observation on the better preparation of the Rohit Sharma-led team ahead of the quadrennial big bash.

title: India's Bharti Enterprises backs space connectivity giant
description: The newly established entity, headquartered in Paris, will have Bharti Enterprises as its primary shareholder, owning 21.2 per cent of the shares.

title: ‘Feel dumber each time I hear you': Haley vs Ramaswamy at GOP debate
'If BJP thinks ...': Danish Ali's jibe over Bidhuri's remarks
description: BSP MP Danish Ali criticized the BJP for giving poll duty to Ramesh Bhiduri, the MP who made derogatory remarks against him. Danish Ali demanded that the BJP should make public Bidhuri's reply to party's show-cause notice. Meanwhile, Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla has referred the matter to the Privileges Committee following complaints from Ali and other opposition MPs. Several BJP MPs also accused Ali of inciting Bhiduri and requested the Speaker to investigate.

title: 'Welcome' CBI probe into bungalow renovation: Kejriwal
description: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has registered a preliminary enquiry to look into alleged "irregularities and misconduct" by unidentified public servants of the Delhi government in connection with the construction of a new official residence for the chief minister, officials said on Wednesday.

title: 'Even if it doesn't wake up ...': Isro on efforts to reconnect with rover
description: Even as Isro is awaiting a signal from Chandrayaan-3's Pragyan rover and Vikram lander, the space agency's chairman S Somanath has said that it won't be a problem even if they fail to wake up.Speaking at a press conference, Somanath said that that Chandrayaan-3's rover, which is currently in sleep mode, has achieved what was expected from it in the mission.The Isro chief said it will wake up if its electronic circuits have not been damaged due to the extreme weather on the moon.

title: Tom Brady reveals weight loss journey: 'I am down about 10 pounds'
description: Former NFL quarterback Tom Brady has discussed his focus on physical health since retiring from professional football. He emphasized the importance of prioritizing physical and mental well-being and making smart choices for a fulfilling life. While he hasn't ruled out a return to the field, Brady has been enjoying his retirement, spending time with family and embracing a balanced lifestyle.

title: British actor who played Dumbledore in Harry Potter, dies aged 82
description: Popularly known for essaying the iconic role of professor Albus Dumbledore in the "Harry Potter" franchise,  British-Irish actor Michael Gambon, passed away on Thursday. He was 82 years old. He died peacefully in hospital, PA Media reported citing a family statement.

title: UP teacher orders Muslim student to slap Hindu mate, arrested
description: On the basis of a complaint filed by the Hindu boy's father, the teacher, Shaista, was booked under IPC sections 153A (promoting enmity between different groups on grounds of religion, race, etc) and 323 (voluntarily causing hurt), Additional SP Shrish Chandra said.

title: Swaminathan Research Foundation shut due to lack of funds
description: ​​"He came to my village Waifad and had started a centre for MS Swaminathan Research Foundation along with a soil testing lab there. The centre shut down in 2015 when the new government stopped grants to it," says Vijay Jawandhia, a veteran farm activist from Wardha and former Shetkari Sangathana leader.

title: 'ScarED, rattlED': Abhishek's dig at ED after fresh summons
description: Trinamool Congress MP Abhishek Banerjee has criticized the Enforcement Directorate (ED) for scheduling his questioning on days that clash with his public engagements. He revealed that the ED has summoned him for questioning on October 3, which coincides with a Trinamool delegation's meeting with the Union minister and their visit to Rajghat in New Delhi. Abhishek claimed that tis is the second time in a month that his questioning date coincides with his political engagements.

title: Sensex sinks 610 points: Why markets saw sharp fall today
description: Driven primarily by higher crude prices and rising global interest rates, both sensex and Nifty reversed early morning gains on Thursday and witnessed a sharp fall. The information technology and consumer sectors mainly led the market decline.The BSE benchmark sensex plunged 610 points to close at 65,508 while Nifty fell 193 points to end at 19,524.

title: Taiwan unveils 'sea monster'; nonsense, says China
description: Taiwan has unveiled its first domestically built submarine, named 'Narwhal', as part of efforts to boost its naval defense capabilities amid a growing threat from China. The submarine, with a price tag of $1.53 billion, will be armed with US-manufactured torpedoes and incorporate a combat system from Lockheed Martin. Details about its size and capability have not been disclosed due to security concerns. China's defense ministry criticized the move, calling it "idiotic nonsense".

title: Why Noida Airport has increased its passenger traffic forecast
description: Noida International Airport: Christoph Schnellmann, CEO of Noida Airport, attributed the optimistic outlook to the rapid rebound of Indian air travel and substantial aircraft orders placed by Indian carriers.

title: UP STF arrests Abdul Samad alias Saddam from Delhi
description: Special DG, Law and Order, Prashant Kumar, said that Abdul was under surveillance and an informer disclosed his location at DDA Flats opposite Select City Walk Mall in Malviya Nagar, Delhi, to an STF unit.

title: Ujjain rape horror: MP police detain four more people
description: The police in Madhya Pradesh's Ujjain on Thursday detained four persons and were interrogating an auto rickshaw driver in connection with the rape of the 12-year-old who was found lying in an unconscious state in a pool of blood in front of an Ashram in Barnagar of Ujjain two days ago.

title: Mystery Russian plane in North Korea stokes concerns
description: Tracking data from FlightRadar24 shows the Russian Air Force Ilyushin IL-62M flying from Moscow to Pyongyang, arriving on Tuesday morning. The tail number on the plane indicates it was the same aircraft Russia sent to North Korea in August, just days after Defense Minister Sergei Shoigu traveled to Pyongyang and was guided by Kim through a collection of his country’s latest weaponry.

title: Haldiram’s packaged snacks sales hit $1.1 billion
description: Haldiram's surpassed PepsiCo in India's snack market roughly five years ago to become the country’s largest snack brand. Since then, the gap in sales has continued to widen.

title: UP leg of Rahul’s yatra to commence from Ayodhya?
description: Will Congress's Wayanad MP Rahul Gandhi start the UP leg of his Bharat Jodo Yatra 2. 0 from Ayodhya? The possibility is being explored very seriously, say Congress sources.​

title: BMW iX1 electric launched in India at Rs 66.9 lakh
description: The EV uses floor floor-mounted 66.4 kWh lithium-ion battery pack and has a claimed range of 440 km (WLTP) in one full charge. The iX1 comes with a BMW 11 kW wall box charger which takes 6.3 hours to fully charge the battery. The iX1 also features a Lane Departure warning, cruise control with brake function, automatic emergency braking and pedestrian protection.

title: National highways to be pothole-free by December
description: Nitin Gadkari, the Union Minister for Road Transport and Highways, has set a deadline of December 2023 to make all national highways potholes free.

title: Vande Bharat sleeper trains project on track
description: Vande Bharat sleeper trains: Earlier this year, an RVNL official had told TOI that once the contract is signed it will take 2 years for the first prototype of the Vande Bharat sleeper rake to be rolled out.

title: MS Swaminathan, father of India’s green revolution, passes away in Chennai
Dravid optimistic as key players gain match fitness ahead of WC
description: India's cricket coach, Rahul Dravid, expressed relief and optimism as key players, Jasprit Bumrah, KL Rahul, and Shreyas Iyer, made strides in their recoveries and gained match fitness ahead of the ODI World Cup. Dravid emphasized the importance of game-time for these players and the fact that they have been able to get it. Bumrah, who had been sidelined due to a persistent back issue, showcased his return to form by bowling his full quota of overs in the matches against Australia.

title: All-time high record: Hyd’s Balapur Ganesh laddu fetches Rs 27L
description: Hyderabad's popular Balapur Ganesh laddu was auctioned at an all-time record price of Rs 27 lakh this year.  Hyderabad resident Dasari Dayanand Reddy won the laddu. 36 people has participated in the auction.

title: Mouni Roy: The highlight of this year's birthday celebrations
description: Birthday girl Mouni Roy turns a year older today and the celebrations have begun since yesterday! The actress is enjoying her special day in the company of besties Disha Patani and Sonam Bajwa. and hubby Suraj Nabiar  In an exclusive chat with ETimes the actress shares details about her special day.

title: 'Indians now represent over 10% of all US visa applicants worldwide'
description: The US Embassy in New Delhi has processed over 1 million non-immigrant visa applications from India this year, marking a 20% increase from pre-Covid numbers. Indians now represent over 10% of all visa applicants worldwide, with 20% of student visa applicants and 65% of employment visa applicants. The embassy plans to launch a pilot program for domestic visa renewal for qualified employment visa applicants.

title: 'Donald Duck' remark, barb at Jill: Top quotes from 2nd GOP Debate
description: Seven presidential hopefuls gathered at the Reagan Library in California on Wednesday for the second of the party’s primary debates. Early frontrunner Donald Trump skipped the event, just as he did the first. He is 2,000 miles away trying to woo union workers in Michigan amid a labor strike. ​​There were some awkward and downright cringeworthy moments during the debate, from lines that were heavily rehearsed to some clunky retorts.

title: Chandrayaan-3: Not just Moon, study of Earth SHAPE(ing) up well too
description: The scientific instrument on the Chandrayaan-3 propulsion module, called SHAPE, has been sending data about Earth-like features while orbiting the Moon. The data will be used by the Isro  to study exoplanets in the future. The instrument has already provided enough data to meet its objectives, but analysis and discoveries will take several months. The propulsion module, initially meant for transportation, was fitted with SHAPE to maximize its capabilities.

title: Sana Khan and husband Anas react to the ‘Rakhi Sawant-Adil Khan’ controversy; the latter says, “I want them to sort things out and be happy together”
description: Sana Khan and her husband Anas have returned from their first international trip as parents. They were asked about the controversy between Adil Khan and Rakhi Sawant, to which Anas expressed support for both parties and hopes they can reconcile. Sana, however, stated that she wants to stay out of the controversy and doesn't know much about it. Anas also mentioned that he doesn't want to comment on Rakhi's Umrah and her use of Islam. The couple thanked the paparazzi for their time and took pictures with fans.

title: E-rickshaws, e-buses at UP tourist spots soon: CM Yogi
description: Addressing a function on the occasion of World Tourism Day organised at Yogiraj Baba Gambhirnath Auditorium in Gorakhpur, Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath said that electric vehicle (EV) services will be introduced at key tourist spots across the state soon.

title: 9-yr-old boy booked for raping 8-yr-old girl in Lucknow
description: An eight year-old girl was allegedly raped by a nine-year-old boy under Sushant Golf City police station area on Tuesday night, police said on Wednesday.

title: Navy partnering with MSMEs & start-ups for niche techs
description: The Indian Navy is progressing with the development of niche technologies through its Swavlamban initiative. The programme, launched last year, involves collaborating with start-ups and MSMEs to develop technologies such as autonomous weaponized swarms, underwater swarm drones, fire-fighting robots, and more.

title: Asian Games: Indian men's 10m air pistol team strikes gold
description: India's men's 10m air pistol team won a gold medal at the Asian Games, narrowly beating the Chinese team. This victory brings India's total gold medal count in shooting events to four. In addition to the team success, Indian marksmen Sarabjot and Arjun have also qualified for the individual finals, increasing India's chances for more medals. This achievement highlights India's growing prominence in the sport of shooting at the Asian Games.

title: Punjab Cong MLA Sukhpal Singh Khaira arrested in drugs case
description: Khaira alleged that he was arrested in a false case registered against him under NDPS Act at Jalalabad in 2015 in which the Supreme Court had already quashed the summons issued against him. “I am being hounded like this because I have been strongly opposing and exposing the Bhagwant Mann government and the chief minister is nursing personal vendetta against me,” he said.

title: Dozing by train door, man falls off but lands in river 60ft below, survives
description: A man fell into the Koyel river in India after dozing off at the door of a moving train. The man survived as the river had enough water to break his fall. He found himself standing in waist-deep water and was eventually rescued by a team from the Railway Protection Force. The man was found to be fit and conscious and his family was informed of the incident.

title: Asiad: Roshibina wins silver in women's Wushu sanda event
description: Naorem Roshibina Devi of India won a silver medal in the women's 60kg wushu sanda final at the Asian Games. She faced tough competition from Wu Xiaowei of China, the reigning champion in the category. Despite her best efforts, Roshibina was unable to defeat her opponent, but her performance earned her respect and admiration from fans and fellow athletes. This silver medal adds to her list of achievements in wushu sanda.

title: Autoworkers should 'picket' in front of White House: Ramaswamy
‘America’s Got Talent’ finale recap: 11 finalists fight for America’s votes
description: The winner of America's Got Talent 2023, who will receive a $1 million prize, will be announced tomorrow. The latest episode showcased 11 impressive performances from the contestants, with each one giving a tough competition to the others. The judges were amazed by the talent on display and acknowledged that every contestant deserves to be in the running to win. The audience eagerly awaits the final decision, as they continue to vote for their favorites.

title: 'Drunk' helper keeps bag on throttle, causes train mishap in UP
description: Hours after Shakurbasti-Mathura MEMU (04446) broke through the platform of Mathura Junction on Tuesday night, an internal report about the accident has found that a drunk helper had kept his bag on the throttle of the engine in the driving cab which caused a sudden acceleration and it crashed into the platform.An initial joint report prepared by a six-member team has found that this ‘helper’ — Sachin Kumar — had been sent to get the key of the driving trailer coach (DTC) cab.

title: St Bernard abandoned in Gujarat finds home abroad
description: A St Bernard named Athena was abandoned near an Ahmedabad crematorium and fell sick. She was found by kind people and given a new home. After undergoing surgery and intensive physiotherapy, she was adopted by a retired British diplomat and his wife. They renamed her Lady Sybil and she now lives a happy life in Delhi and will soon move to Canada.

title: RJD MP Manoj Jha's 'Thakurs' poem in Parliament triggers political storm in Bihar
description: The poem references 'Thakurs', which local politicians claim is targeting a specific caste. Anand Mohan, a Grand Alliance leader, has expressed his anger and stated that he would not tolerate the humiliation of his community. Jha had recited the poem composed by Om Prakash Valmiki during a debate on the women's reservation bill. Anand Mohan, who recently served a life term in connection with a murder case, is the father of an RJD MLA.

title: India aging rapidly, 60+ will make up 15% of population by 2036: UN
description: According to a new UN report, India is experiencing a rapid increase in its elderly population, while the number of individuals below 15 is declining. By 2046, the number of elderly individuals in India will surpass the number of children aged 0-14.

title: Raped and bleeding, 12-yr-old begs for help in Ujjain, turned away
description: A 12-year-old girl who was raped in Ujjain, India, went door to door seeking help but was ignored by residents. She was found unconscious in front of an ashram after walking 8km. The incident has sparked outrage and prompted the police to take action. The survivor has been referred to a hospital in Indore, and a suspect has been detained.

title: Ariana Madix debuts on ‘Dancing With The Stars', Matt Walsh eliminated
description: The 32nd season of Dancing With The Stars has begun with Ariana Madix making a stunning debut in a red gown. Her performance with partner Pasha Pashkov received high praise. Meanwhile, actor Matt Walsh was eliminated from the show in the first round. Despite the short journey, Walsh expressed gratitude for the support he received. Ariana, who had been out of the spotlight following a breakup, showcased her dancing skills on the show. The rest of the couples will return for "Latin Night" next week.

title: FCU not final arbiter, just flags issue, Centre tells HC
City dengue cases till mid-Sept 2.5x more than '18 & '19 counts
description: The city of Kolkata in India has seen a surge in dengue cases, with over 4,000 cases reported so far, more than double the count from last year. Experts believe this may be due to a cyclical prevalence of the virus, which leads to major outbreaks every few years. Certain neighborhoods in Kolkata, including New Alipore, Lake Gardens, and Garfa, are particularly affected. Precautions taken during the pandemic had initially slowed the spread of dengue, but with life returning to normal, conditions have become favorable for the virus.

title: Red tape delays return of 1,400 stolen idols from US
description: Over 1,400 antique idols and artifacts stolen from India and currently in the US have not been returned to India, despite being cleared for repatriation four months ago. The delay is being blamed on procedures and budget constraints by the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI). India Pride Project, a non-profit organization working on reclaiming such idols, criticizes ASI for its poor record in protecting and retrieving stolen artifacts. ASI denies the allegations and states that India is the only nation that physically sends experts to validate the authenticity of the idols.
